column1: You need at least a year of paper trading. And get to the point of being consistently profitable. Options are extraordinarily detailed and you have to learn the nuances of IV, delta, order flow dynamics, etc. Itâ€™s honestly better to learn to trade SPY or /ES to get some daily practice and repetition. Check out eminplayer.net and Shadowtrader to get an introduction to a systematic trading strategy. The options world is a little complicated with endless possibilities and that can be quite daunting. Learning how to consistently read and trade SPY is a great way to build fundamentals which will definitely help you later with options swing trades.
